verses.text:
And unto Adam he said, Because thou hast hearkened unto the voice of thy wife, and hast eaten of the tree, of which I commanded thee, saying, Thou shalt not eat of it: cursed
is the ground for thy sake; in sorrow shalt thou eat
of it all the days of thy life;

And Laban said to Jacob, Behold this heap, and behold
this
 pillar, which I have cast betwixt me and thee;

But in this will we consent unto you: If ye will be as we
be,
 that every male of you be circumcised;

And all countries came into Egypt to Joseph for to buy
corn;
 because that the famine was so sore in all lands.

And Joseph said unto them the third day, This do, and live;
for
 I fear God:

And we said unto my lord, The lad cannot leave his father: for
if he should leave his father,
his father would die.

But as for you, ye thought evil against me;
but God meant it unto good, to bring to pass, as
it is this day, to save much people alive.

Send therefore now,
and gather thy cattle, and all that thou hast in the field;
for upon every man and beast which shall be found in the field, and shall not be brought home, the hail shall come down upon them, and they shall die.

And Moses said unto him, As soon as I am gone out of the city, I will spread abroad my hands unto the LORD;
and the thunder shall cease, neither shall there be any more hail; that thou mayest know how that the earth
is the LORD’S.

And Moses stretched forth his rod over the land of Egypt, and the LORD brought an east wind upon the land all that day, and all
that night;
and when it was morning, the east wind brought the locusts.

And the son of an Israelitish woman, whose father
was an Egyptian, went out among the children of Israel: and this son of the Israelitish
woman and a man of Israel strove together in the camp;

And if
a man sanctify unto the LORD a field which he hath bought, which
is not of the fields of his possession;

Take ye the sum of all the congregation of the children of Israel, after their families, by the house of their fathers, with the number of
their
 names, every male by their polls;

And a man lie with her carnally, and it be hid from the eyes of her husband, and be kept close, and she be defiled, and
there be no witness against her, neither she be taken
with the manner;

This
is the law of jealousies, when a wife goeth aside
to another instead of her husband, and is defiled;

From Aroer, that
is upon the bank of the river Arnon, and the city that
is in the midst of the river, and all the plain of Medeba unto Dibon;

And their coast was from Aroer, that
is on the bank of the river Arnon, and the city that
is in the midst of the river, and all the plain by Medeba;

And the name of Hebron before
was Kirjath-arba;
which Arba was a great man among the Anakims. And the land had rest from war.

This then was the lot of the tribe of the children of Judah by their families;
even to the border of Edom the wilderness of Zin southward
was the uttermost part of the south coast.

And I sent the hornet before you, which drave them out from before you,
even the two kings of the Amorites;
but not with thy sword, nor with thy bow.

They looked, but
there was none to save;
even unto the LORD, but he answered them not.

Then she said, I desire one small petition of thee;
I pray thee,
 say me not nay. And the king said unto her, Ask on, my mother: for I will not say thee nay.

If there be in the land famine, if there be pestilence, blasting, mildew, locust,
or if there be caterpiller; if their enemy besiege them in the land of their cities; whatsoever plague, whatsoever sickness
there be;

And when the LORD saw that they humbled themselves, the word of the LORD came to Shemaiah, saying, They have humbled themselves;
therefore
 I will not destroy them, but I will grant them some deliverance; and my wrath shall not be poured out upon Jerusalem by the hand of Shishak.

They cause
him to go naked without clothing, and they take away the sheaf
from the hungry;

As God liveth,
who hath taken away my judgment; and the Almighty,
who hath vexed my soul;

All the while my breath
is in me, and the spirit of God
is in my nostrils;

The flood breaketh out from the inhabitant;
even the waters
 forgotten of the foot: they are dried up, they are gone away from men.

When his candle shined upon my head,
and when by his light I walked
through darkness;

As I was in the days of my youth, when the secret of God
was
 upon my tabernacle;

If I beheld the sun when it shined, or the moon walking
in
 brightness;

He looketh upon men, and
if any say, I have sinned, and perverted
that which was right, and it profited me not;

And if
they be bound in fetters,
and be holden in cords of affliction;

Teach us what we shall say unto him;
for we cannot order
our speech by reason of darkness.

As a dream when
one awaketh;
so, O Lord, when thou awakest, thou shalt despise their image.

Lift up thy feet unto the perpetual desolations;
even all
that the enemy hath done wickedly in the sanctuary.

So that he forsook the tabernacle of Shiloh, the tent
which
 he placed among men;

Riches and honour
are with me;
yea, durable riches and righteousness.

He that keepeth the commandment keepeth his own soul;
but
 he that despiseth his ways shall die.

Thus saith the LORD, thy redeemer, and he that formed thee from the womb, I
am the LORD that maketh all
things; that stretcheth forth the heavens alone; that spreadeth abroad the earth by myself;

Because I knew that thou
art obstinate, and thy neck
is an iron sinew, and thy brow brass;

Therefore the redeemed of the LORD shall return, and come with singing unto Zion; and everlasting joy
shall be upon their head: they shall obtain gladness and joy;
and sorrow and mourning shall flee away.

This
city shall not be your caldron, neither shall ye be the flesh in the midst thereof;
but I will judge you in the border of Israel:

Say now to the rebellious house, Know ye not what these
things mean? tell
them, Behold, the king of Babylon is come to Jerusalem, and hath taken the king thereof, and the princes thereof, and led them with him to Babylon;

Therefore their goods shall become a booty, and their houses a desolation: they shall also build houses, but not inhabit
them;
 and they shall plant vineyards, but not drink the wine thereof.

And flocks shall lie down in the midst of her, all the beasts of the nations: both the cormorant and the bittern shall lodge in the upper lintels of it;
their voice shall sing in the windows; desolation
shall be in the thresholds: for he shall uncover the cedar work.
